## .NET MAUI Shell Navigation with `IQueryAttributable`

**1. Passing a simple string (Product ID):**

```csharp
// Navigate from ProductListPage code-behind or VM
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"ProductDetailsPage?productId={product.Id}");
```

**2. Passing a complex object (full Product):**

```csharp
var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
{
    { "product", selectedProduct }   // object parameter
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("ProductDetailsPage", navParams);
```

**3. Receiving both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Simple string parameter (arrives as string)
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var idObj))
            _productId = idObj.ToString();

        // Complex object parameter (arrives as the original type)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var prodObj) && prodObj is Product p)
            _product = p;

        LoadProduct();
    }

    private async void LoadProduct()
    {
        if (_product is not null)
            // Already have the full object â€” bind directly
            CurrentProduct = _product;
        else if (_productId is not null)
            // Only have the ID â€” fetch from service
            CurrentProduct = await _productService.GetByIdAsync(_productId);
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel to the page and register the route:**

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();

// AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute("ProductDetailsPage", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| Navigation | `GoToAsync($"...?key={val}")` | `GoToAsync("...", Dictionary<string,object>)` |
| Survives URL serialization | âś… Yes | âťŚ No (transient only) |
| Type in `ApplyQueryAttributes` | `string` | Original CLR type |

Shell calls `ApplyQueryAttributes` on the page's `BindingContext` automatically if it implements `IQueryAttributable` â€” no `[QueryProperty]` attributes needed.
